# Template for a machine-specific Cargo config.
#
# The real `config.toml` is intentionally gitignored: it holds ABSOLUTE paths
# that are valid only on one machine, and committing it broke Windows builds
# (the macOS path resolved to C:/Users/.../_NOAV and failed with "access denied").
#
# You usually do NOT need this file:
#   - Windows / Linux: plain `cargo tauri dev` and `cargo tauri build` work as-is.
#   - macOS (managed, Defender/DLP): prefer the wrapper `./desktop/tauri.sh dev`,
#     which sets the same env without any committed config.
#
# Only create a local `config.toml` (copy this file, drop the .example suffix,
# and replace the paths) if you want plain `cargo tauri dev` on a Defender-managed
# Mac where the linker is blocked from the default temp dir. Point both the Rust
# target dir and TMPDIR at a Defender-excluded folder:
#
# [build]
# target-dir = "/Users/<you>/_NOAV/XcodeDerivedData/cargo-target"
#
# [env]
# TMPDIR = { value = "/Users/<you>/_NOAV/XcodeDerivedData/tmp", force = true }
